dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Names in Admin3 and 4 with ALL CAPS and spaces in between letters were made Proper Case. 2. Created and populated reference name field. Names with apostrophes now have a reference name without apostrophes. 3. Roman numerals in Admin3 and 4 names were made Proper Case. 4. Missing units "Medari", "Traji" and "Sawah" were imported from layer "idn_bnd_adm4_2017_bps_a.shp". 5. Approximately 960 multipart sliver errors were found and fixed. 6. "Taja Urap" was given p-code "ID6211050015", changed from "ID62110ID621105001550". 7. As instructed by UNOCHA, ITOS has given unique numbered names to these units: The 2 Admin4 units named "Merlung" bordering each other in Admin3 "Merlung", the 2 Admin4 units named "Panipahan" bordering each other in Admin3 "Pasir Limau Kapas", the 2 Admin4 units named "Sorkam Kanan" bordering each other in Admin3 "Sorkam Barat", the 2 Admin4 units named "Terusan" bordering each other in Admin3 "Maro Sebo Ilir", the 2 Admin4 units named "Sawagumu" bordering each other in Admin3 "Sorong Utara". 8.102 gap errors and 9 overlap errors were fixed. 9. Fixed 4 nesting errors between admin layers.
The following was found but not addressed in this version: 1. The slashes and parentheses in some names suggest the presence of alternate names that should be seperated and placed in AltName fields. 2. Admin4 includes some odd geometry for the island "Gonone". A thin border attributed as "Pulau" surrounds it. This could represent temporary borders and so has been kept as-is.
